<p><strong>Sydney, {{ date | readableDate }}</strong>
<p>Oracle and OneQode today announce their partnership to bring joint cloud & infrastructure solutions to enterprise customers in the Asia-Pacific region, with a particular focus on gaming and high-performance applications.</p>
<div class="callout col-xs-12 p-2 my-2" id="key-facts">
	<h2>Key facts</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>The two companies will develop integrated solutions for customers in the Asia-Pacific region</li>
		<li>Oracle will integrate OneQode’s high-performance cloud and network services into their Oracle Cloud Infrastructure (OCI) solutions offering</li>
		<li>OneQode will integrate Oracle’s services, including OCI’s leading database and security products, into their cloud platform</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<p>Digitisation is occurring rapidly in Asia-Pacific and performance demands are similarly increasing post-COVID. Oracle is leading the way as the partner of choice for enterprise customers across the region, leveraging its extensive cloud, database and security offerings. OneQode are addressing emergent needs in growing niche industries with a latency-optimised telecommunications network, high-performance compute platform and a new Asia-Pacific hub on the island of Guam.</p>
<p>The companies will jointly develop whole-of-region solutions for game industry and enterprise customers, integrating their respective service offerings and exploring wider opportunities to deliver high-performance solutions for customers.</p>
